<L><PB N="232" REF="249">Will brighter &s;hine, its clouds withdrawn:</L>
<L>Or, is thy morn of &s;un-&s;hine pa&s;t,</L>
<L>With clouds thy ev'ning's overca&s;t:<MILESTONE N="380"></L>
<L>Would&s;t of its brightne&s;s know th'amount?</L>
<L>Bring morn and ev'ning to account.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Stands nature then, &s;o long abus'd,</L>
<L>Of ab&s;tract evil thus excus'd;</L>
<L>As little truth is under&s;tood <MILESTONE N="385"></L>
<L>By tho&s;e, who hold all nature <HI>good.</HI></L>
